SEMDL CLI Help

1. Overview
- `ssd` validates, explains, transforms, and updates `.ssd` and `.ssm` assets.
- This help output is the canonical entrypoint for CLI guidance.
- Formal grammar lives in `docs/cli.ebnf`.
- Acceptance manifests live in `docs/examples/testcases/`.
- Requirements live in `docs/requirements.md`.

2. Table of Contents
- `ssd help overview`
- `ssd help toc`
- `ssd help grammar`
- `ssd help reference [subcommand]`
- `ssd help recipes [topic]`
- `ssd help samples`
- `ssd help troubleshooting`

3. Grammar
- Root: `ssd <subcommand> ...`
- Root help: `ssd help [topic] [target]`
- Global help: `ssd --help`
- Subcommand help: `ssd <subcommand> --help`
- See `docs/cli.ebnf` for the formal grammar.

4. Reference
- `check`: validate syntax and references for a document set
- `explain`: show the merged semantic view for an entity id
- `set`: update one inline or sidecar field
- `remove`: remove one target or fail on unsafe removal
- `annotate`: add rationale/caveat/todo-like notes
- `split`: move sidecar-eligible metadata out of inline form
- `merge`: produce a merged inline view
- `help`: navigate this help system

5. Reverse Lookup
- Validate a document: `ssd check <file>`
- Explain an assertion: `ssd explain <id> <file>`
- Preview an inline edit: `ssd set path:<id>.<field> <value> --dry-run <file>`
- Preview a sidecar annotation: `ssd annotate id:<id> rationale <text> --target sidecar --dry-run <file>`
- Understand an option error: `ssd help grammar`
- Understand a selector-layer error: `ssd help recipes wrong-layer`

6. Samples
- `ssd check docs/examples/minimal.ssd`
- `ssd explain A1 docs/examples/minimal.ssd`
- `ssd help reference check`
- `ssd set meta:A1.confidence 0.91 --dry-run docs/examples/minimal.ssd`

7. Cautions, Known Bugs, Reporting
- In this initial slice, `search`, `extract`, `similarity`, `add`, and `normalize` are not implemented yet.
- Update flows are acceptance-driven and still incomplete for full file rewriting.
- Report problems with the command, argv, input paths, expected output, actual output, and related golden file.
- Preferred reporting path: repository issue or change request with a reproducing CLI case.
